# pyenv
#   For a library or binary, you wish to ignore these files by default.
#   For managed Python projects, you may want to include these files.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#1191, it is recommended to not ignore Pipfile.lock.
#   If you are part of a development team or objects to track it, see:
#   https://pipenv.pypa.io/en/latest/install/#pipfile-lock-errors-and-warnings
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include poetry.lock in version control.
#   https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-file-to-version-control
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include pdm.lock in version control.
